{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Unpredictable hours and on-call shifts have kindled a nationwide movement to give part-time workers more rights.", "abstract": "Growing national movement fueled by women's and labor groups seeks to curb workplace scheduling practices that impose part-time work or unpredictable schedules on employees, wreaking havoc with responsibilities like child and elder care;  Vermont and San Francisco have adopted laws giving workers right to request flexible or predictable schedules, and New York City Comptroller Scott M Stringer is pressing City Council to take up such legislation.", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Steven", "role": "reported", "lastname": "GREENHOUSE", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By STEVEN GREENHOUSE", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/16/business/a-push-to-give-steadier-shifts-to-part-timers.html", "lead_paragraph": "Unpredictable hours and on-call shifts have kindled a nationwide movement to give part-time workers more rights.", "headline": {"main": "A Push to Give Steadier Shifts to Part-Timers", "print_headline": "A Push to Give Steadier Shifts to Part-Timers"}, "_id": "53c5c36038f0d844fb7d829d", "word_count": "1373", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work1/Work1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work1/Work1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work1/Work1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work1/Work1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work2/Work2-thumbStandard-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/07/16/business/Work2/Work2-thumbStand